exports[`stepRouteDrive given: [case4] vibecheck snapshots when: [t2] no route bound (direct mode) then: output matches snapshot 1`] = `
"🦉 where were we?

🗿 route.drive
   ├─ where do we go?
   │  ├─ route = .behavior/v2026_02_27.clearer-guidance
   │  └─ stone = 1.vision
   │
   ├─ are we there yet? if so, run
   │  └─ rhx route.stone.set --stone 1.vision --as passed
   │
   ├─ here's the stone
   │  ├─
   │  │
   │  │  illustrate the vision implied in the wish .behavior/v2026_02_27.clearer-guidance/0.wish.md
   │  │
   │  │  emit into .behavior/v2026_02_27.clearer-guidance/1.vision.md
   │  │
   │  │  ---
   │  │
   │  │  paint a picture of what the world looks like when this wish is fulfilled
   │  │
   │  │  testdrive the contract we propose via realworld examples
   │  │
   │  │  specifically,
   │  │
   │  │  ## the outcome world
   │  │
   │  │  - what does a day-in-the-life look like with this in place?
   │  │  - what's the before/after contrast?
   │  │  - what's the "aha" moment where the value clicks?
   │  │
   │  │  ## user experience
   │  │
   │  │  - what usecases do folks fulfill? what goals?
   │  │  - what contract inputs & outputs do they leverage?
   │  │  - what would it look like to leverage them?
   │  │  - what timelines do they go through?
   │  │
   │  │  ## mental model
   │  │
   │  │  - how would users describe this to a friend?
   │  │  - what analogies or metaphors fit?
   │  │  - what terms would they use vs what terms would we use?
   │  │
   │  │  ## evaluation
   │  │
   │  │  - how well does it solve the goals?
   │  │  - what are the pros? the cons?
   │  │  - what edgecases exist and how do our contracts keep users in a pit of success?
   │  │
   │  │  uncover anything awkward
   │  │
   │  └─
   │
   └─ are we there yet? if so, run
      └─ rhx route.stone.set --stone 1.vision --as passed"
`;
